interfaces.label: AuthenticatedUser
description: Represents the currently authenticated user.

children.label: authentication_realm
description: The name and type of the Realm that has authenticated the user.

children.label: lookup_realm
description: The name and type of the Realm where the user information were retrieved from.

children.label: authentication_provider
description: The authentication provider that used to authenticate user.

children.label: authentication_type
description: The AuthenticationType used by ES to authenticate the user.

children.label: elastic_cloud_user
description: Indicates whether user is authenticated via Elastic Cloud built-in SAML realm.

children.label: profile_uid
description: User profile ID of this user.

interfaces.label: AuthenticationProvider
description: Type and name tuple to identify provider used to authenticate user.

children.label: type
description: Type of the Kibana authentication provider.

children.label: name
description: Name of the Kibana authentication provider (arbitrary string).

children.label: field_security
signature: { grant?: string[] | undefined; except?: string[] | undefined; } | undefined

interfaces.label: SecurityLicenseFeatures
description: Describes Security plugin features that depend on license.

children.label: showLogin
description: Indicates whether we show login page or skip it.

children.label: allowLogin
description: Indicates whether we allow login or disable it on the login page.

children.label: showLinks
description: Indicates whether we show security links throughout the kibana app.

children.label: showRoleMappingsManagement
description: Indicates whether we show the Role Mappings UI.

children.label: allowAccessAgreement
description: Indicates whether we allow users to access agreement UI and acknowledge it.

children.label: allowAuditLogging
description: Indicates whether we allow logging of audit events.

children.label: allowRoleDocumentLevelSecurity
description: Indicates whether we allow users to define document level security in roles.

children.label: allowRoleFieldLevelSecurity
description: Indicates whether we allow users to define field level security in roles.

children.label: allowRoleRemoteIndexPrivileges
description: Indicates whether we allow users to define remote index privileges in roles.

children.label: allowRbac
description: Indicates whether we allow Role-based access control (RBAC).

children.label: allowSubFeaturePrivileges
description: Indicates whether we allow sub-feature privileges.

children.label: allowUserProfileCollaboration
description: Indicates whether we allow user profile collaboration features (suggest and privileges checks APIs).

children.label: layout
description: Describes the layout of the login form if it's displayed.

interfaces.label: User
description: A set of fields describing Kibana user.

children.label: metadata
signature: { _reserved: boolean; _deprecated?: boolean | undefined; _deprecated_reason?: string | undefined; } | undefined

interfaces.label: UserProfile
description:
IMPORTANT:

The types in this file are duplicated at
`packages/kbn-user-profile-components/src/user_profile.ts`

When making changes please ensure to keep both files in sync.

Describes basic properties stored in user profile.

children.label: uid
description: Unique ID for of the user profile.

children.label: enabled
description: Indicates whether user profile is enabled or not.

children.label: user
description: Information about the user that owns profile.

children.label: data
description: User specific data associated with the profile.

interfaces.label: UserProfileUserInfo
description: Basic user information returned in user profile.

children.label: username
description: Username of the user.

children.label: email
description: Optional email of the user.

children.label: full_name
description: Optional full name of the user.

interfaces.label: UserProfileUserInfoWithSecurity
description: Extended user information returned in user profile (both basic and security related properties).

children.label: roles
description: List of the user roles.

children.label: realm_name
description: Name of the Elasticsearch security realm that was used to authenticate user.

children.label: realm_domain
description:
Optional name of the security domain that Elasticsearch security realm that was
used to authenticate user resides in (if any).

interfaces.label: UserProfileWithSecurity
description: Describes all properties stored in user profile (both basic and security related properties).

children.label: user
description: Information about the user that owns profile.

children.label: labels
description:
User specific _searchable_ labels associated with the profile. Note that labels are considered
security related field since it's going to be used to store user's space ID.

interfaces.label: UserRealm
description: An Elasticsearch realm that was used to resolve and authenticate the user.

children.label: name
description: Arbitrary name of the security realm.

children.label: type
description: Type of the security realm (file, native, saml etc.).

misc.label: LoginLayout
description: Represents types of login form layouts.

description: Placeholder for data stored in user profile.
